    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-10T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-10T08:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/212: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VSRG1"
                            type="from">Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary
                            of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-10T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 10, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 10—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>183. Consulate’s 167, May 3, 11 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">noon?</hi>]<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d10fn8">Not printed.</note> The Council (<persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_MJ1">Matos</persName>, Guatemala, presiding for this
                    session) this morning received and transmitted to the Assembly the <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> Report dated April 30:<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d10fn9">League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                            Journal</hi>, Special Supplement No. 102, pp. 30–32.</note> The
                    representative of Japan made an oral reservation maintaining Japan’s position
                    respecting the nonapplicability of article 15.<note n="10" xml:id="d10fn10">Of
                        the Covenant of the League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Treaties,
                            Conventions, etc., Between the United States of America and Other
                            Powers</hi>, 1910–1923 (Washington, Government Printing Office, 1923),
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">viii</hi>, p. 3336.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center"> . . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VSRG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
